social_posts.post_text:
Posting the front and back cover of my tabloid for my new act “Scandal”. Women in the news are spoken about with language that has sexist connotations and are more likely to be featured in stories about accidents, scandals, domestic abuse, and are held to different standards than men. It’s also time to hold news media accountable for rising transphobia. Hate crimes are rising and the question of trans and queer people belonging in public life is rife. In homes around the world, trans people are the butt of jokes. Media can’t be trusted to report on women, trans, and queers. Let’s do something differently, let’s take our power back. 🤘
Tabloid created & designed by @duanedi 
Featuring a cameo from my lovely burlesque ex-husband 
And a big thank you to @mistyportugal for printing these off for me during a busy week! 💖🥰✨
#dragisart #burlesqueisart #trans #lgbtq #dragqueen #draglesque #queerlesque #nonbinary #queerartist #mtlburlesque #femme #performance #queer #pride

From DRAG HEALS Season 3, talking about my childhood being able to wear a wig only on Halloween, dreaming to be Elvira! Every Halloween I was allowed to buy a wig; it was always a cheap, black plastic wig, but it made me feel SO GLAMOROUS! We only had two TV stations, however, sometimes we could get Global TV if the TV antenna was bent *just* right, and late night I would catch glimpses of
“Elvira, Mistress of The Dark”movie. And now in the past 7 months I’ve created an act as a bearded Elvira and hosting burlesque shows! Excited to keep working and growing my Elvira cosplay!

Whenever I perform on a Sunday , I think of Lili St. Cyr. There used to be a law in Montréal where you couldn’t str*p on a Sunday. Lili was famous for waiting until midnight to perform, when it technically became Monday. And it was well known that come Monday morning, there would be many tired businessmen. Behold your Patron Saint of Sundays: Lili St. Cyr 🤘💋

I've been having this conversation for a few days now when someone first asked me "What's the future of drag?". I have to say it's the next generation of performers.
I think we tend to get caught in the binary- there's drag kings and there's drag queens. But there's a whole spectrum in between. The younger generation gets this.
It's drag and genderfuckery. No labels. It's just performance. And I live! There will always be a place for the binary but to see this explosion of drag fvckery warms my icy heart. The future is queer! 🤘
